cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.GT, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the generation of synthetic images of humans with control over appearance, pose, and shape parameters. This involves the use of 3D reasoning for both people and scenes, and the creation of realistic collages by modeling perspective effects, occlusion, scene semantics, and relative scales. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by graphics (cs.GR) and geometric topology (cs.GT). Multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also possible categories, given the use of parametric representation and appearance compositing.
